                  "key": "ai.response.text",
                  "value": {
                    "stringValue": "Let the **ball** cost \\(x\\) dollars.\n\n1. **Bat cost:** “The bat costs \\$1.00 more than the ball,” so the bat costs  \n   \\[\n   x + 1.00\n   \\]\n2. **Total cost:** The bat and ball cost \\$1.10 total, so  \n   \\[\n   x + (x + 1.00) = 1.10\n   \\]\n3. **Combine like terms:**  \n   \\[\n   2x + 1.00 = 1.10\n   \\]\n4. **Subtract 1.00 from both sides:**  \n   \\[\n   2x = 1.10 - 1.00 = 0.10\n   \\]\n5. **Divide by 2:**  \n   \\[\n   x = \\frac{0.10}{2} = 0.05\n   \\]\n\n✅ **The ball costs \\$0.05 (5 cents).**"
